 Nigeria has recorded 108 new Coronavirus cases, bringing the total number of confirmed infections in the country to 981. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control disclosed this in a tweet on Thursday. The new cases are spread across Lagos, Kwara, Plateau, Ogun, Borno, Akwa Ibom and FCT. The agency said, “108 new cases of ‪#COVID19‬ have been reported; 78 in Lagos, 14 in FCT, five in Ogun, four in Gombe, three Borno, two in Akwa Ibom, one in Kwara, one in Plateau. “As at 11:30 pm 23rd April, there are 981 confirmed cases of ‪#COVID19‬ reported in Nigeria. Discharged: 197, deaths: 31.”  108 new cases of #COVID19 have been reported;78 in Lagos14 in FCT5 in Ogun4 in Gombe3 Borno2 in Akwa Ibom1 in Kwara1 in Plateau As at 11:30 pm 23rd April there are 981 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria.Discharged: 197Deaths: 31#TakeResponsibility pic.twitter.com/cq7STlnHGJ 